OL,6,F'You probably can't tell us why you
OL,7,Fdid it': Victim's mother addresses his
OL,8,Fattackers
OL,10,FIn a victim impact statement to the
OL,11,Fcourt the victim's mother described
OL,12,Fthe impact the attack had on him and
OL,13,Fhis family.
OL,15,FShe recounted the moment she found out
OL,16,Fher son had been attacked and
OL,17,Fremembered rushing to hospital finding
OL,18,Fhim with 'catastrophic' injuries.
OL,20,FShe described her son, before the
OL,21,Fattack, as being 'outgoing and bubbly'.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
